.TH NQIFTOP 1 "2026-06-10" "qiftop 0.2.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nqiftop \- ncurses real\-time network traffic monitor (qiftop)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nqiftop
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nqiftop
is the terminal (ncurses) front\-end of qiftop. It shows the same two live
views as the GUI \(em
.B Interfaces
and
.B Connections
\(em over SSH or on a headless box, with no X11/Wayland dependency.
.PP
Like
.BR qiftop (1),
it tries to use the privileged
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
on D\-Bus. If no agent is reachable it falls back to in\-process capture,
which needs root for per\-connection data.
.PP
The
.B Connections
view always shows the flow (protocol + endpoints) and its RX/TX rate and
totals. When the agent advertises attribution, two more columns appear by
default:
.B Process
.RB ( "comm [pid]" ,
or the reason a flow has no local process \(em
.IR forwarded ", " orphaned ", " "no socket" )
and
.B Container
.RB ( runtime\fR:\fIname ).
They need the agent's
.I process\-attribution\-wire
and
.I container\-attribution\-wire
capabilities respectively; under in\-process capture (no agent) they stay
hidden. Each is hidden automatically while grouping by that key (the group
header already names it). Toggle them from the
.B f
(Fields) or
.B S
(Settings) panel.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interval " " \fIms\fR
Poll/refresh interval in milliseconds (default 1000). A command\-line value
overrides the saved setting.
.TP
.B \-\-theme " " \fIname\fR
Colour theme:
.BR dark ", " light ", " colorblind ", " mono
(default
.BR dark ).
Cycle live with
.BR z .
.TP
.B \-\-view " " \fItab\fR
Initial tab:
.B interfaces
or
.BR connections .
Default: last used.
.TP
.B \-\-group " " \fImode\fR
Group the Connections view:
.BR off ", " interface ", " process ", " container .
Default: last used. Cycle live with
.BR g .
.TP
.B \-\-session
Talk to the agent on the
.B session
bus instead of the system bus (development).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-agent
Skip the agent and capture in\-process (needs root).
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Diagnostics to stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help ", " \-v ", " \-\-version
Show help / version and exit.
.SH INTERACTIVE KEYS
.SS Navigation and views
.TP
.BR j ", " k ", " \(da ", " \(ua
Move the cursor down / up.
.TP
.BR PgUp ", " PgDn ", " ^U ", " ^D
Move the cursor by a full / half page.
.TP
.BR Home ", " End ", " G
Jump to the top / bottom.
.TP
.BR Tab ", " 1 ", " 2
Switch view (Interfaces / Connections).
.TP
.BR Enter ", " Space ", " l ", " \(->
Show details for the selected row. In the detail panel,
.BR j ", " k
and the arrow keys move to the previous/next row; other keys close it.
.TP
.BR h ", " \(<-
Reserved in the main table. In panels, vim keys and arrows navigate or
adjust values as shown in the footer.
.SS Sorting and grouping
.TP
.B s
Cycle the sort field.
.TP
.B f
Open the Fields panel: pick the sort field
.RB ( Enter " sorts, " r " reverses)"
.B and
toggle column visibility
.RB ( Space
shows/hides the optional Process / Container columns). The panel marks the
active sort field and its direction even when that column is hidden.
.TP
.B r
Reverse the sort order.
.TP
.B g
Cycle connection grouping (off / interface / process / container).
.SS Filtering, display and export
.TP
.B /
Edit a Connections filter expression (see
.BR "FILTER LANGUAGE" ).
.B Enter
applies,
.B Esc
cancels editing or clears an active filter.
.TP
.B p
Pause / resume the display. When paused, the visible snapshot is frozen.
.TP
.B w
Export the current view to a timestamped CSV file in the current working
directory:
.IR qiftop\-interfaces\-YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS.csv
or
.IR qiftop\-connections\-YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS.csv .
.TP
.B z
Cycle the colour theme.
.TP
.B e
Cycle the agent's runtime attribution eagerness
.RB ( default / off / balanced / eager ).
Only effective when the agent advertises the
.I attribution\-eagerness\-hints
capability; the choice is remembered and re\-asserted while nqiftop runs.
.TP
.B S
.RB ( "or " F2 )
Open the Settings panel. Use
.BR "\(ua\(da" / "j" / "k"
to move and
.BR "\(<-" / "\(->" / "h" / "l" / "Space"
to change a value.
.TP
.BR ? ", " F1
Show the key\-binding help overlay.
.TP
.B a
Show the About panel.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.PP
View, sort, grouping, theme, interval, the Process / Container column toggles
and other display settings are saved between runs unless overridden on the
command line.
.SH FILTER LANGUAGE
The Connections filter is a boolean expression language shared with the
GUI. Combine predicates with
.BR and ", " or ", " not
and parentheses.
.PP
.B String fields:
.IR proto ", " src ", " dst ", " host ", " iface ", " family ", " direction ", "
.IR comm ", " runtime ", " container ", " chain_has .
.br
.B Numeric fields:
.IR sport ", " dport ", " port ", " bytes_in / out / total ", "
.IR pkts_in / out / total ", " rate_in / out / total ", " pid ", " uid .
.PP
.B Operators:
.RB ` : '
(string substring / numeric ==),
.RB ` = ' " / " ` != '
(exact / negated),
.RB ` ~ '
(regex),
.RB ` < ' " " ` <= ' " " ` > ' " " ` >= '
(numeric).
Numeric values accept IEC/SI byte suffixes
.RB ( K ", " Ki ", " M ", " Mi ", " G ", " Gi ", " T ", " Ti ).
.PP
.B Examples:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
proto:tcp and port=443
rate_total > 1Mi
host ~ amazonaws and not dport:53
runtime:docker and bytes_out > 100Ki
pid=0
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/qiftop/nqiftop.conf
Per\-user nqiftop settings, separate from the GUI's
.IR qiftop.conf .
.TP
.I ./qiftop-interfaces-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.csv
.TQ
.I ./qiftop-connections-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.csv
CSV exports written by
.BR w .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qiftop (1),
.BR qiftop\-agent (8),
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5),
.BR iftop (8)
